From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] amdgpu: rename ProcessI2cChannelTransaction -> ReadEDIDFromHWAssistedI2C

Mirrors the rename done by ps4gentoo's original 2020 ps4patches mega-commit
(github.com/ps4boot/ps4-linux 1fef36f5a). In current upstream atombios.h:357
the two names are #define aliases for the same ATOM table, so this is
functionally a no-op — the compiled GetIndexIntoMasterTable result is
identical.

Reason for applying anyway:
  - documents which ATOM table name PS4 ATOM is actually built against
    (ReadEDIDFromHWAssistedI2C, per the ps4gentoo investigation)
  - if the macro alias is ever removed in a future upstream sync, this
    patch keeps the PS4 path on the correct table name without us
    having to rediscover the workaround
  - cheap consistency win when grepping our tree against the original
    ps4gentoo reference patches

No behavior change expected from this patch alone.

Source: ps4gentoo 1fef36f5aefd11c594602a98e528184026e146c9 (Dec 2020),
        adapted for our 6.x source layout.

---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/atombios_i2c.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/atombios_i2c.c
@@ -31,7 +31,8 @@

 #define TARGET_HW_I2C_CLOCK 50

-/* these are a limitation of ProcessI2cChannelTransaction not the hw */
+/* limitation of ProcessI2cChannelTransaction / ReadEDIDFromHWAssistedI2C
+ * (these are aliases for the same ATOM table); the limit is in the table args, not the hw */
 #define ATOM_MAX_HW_I2C_WRITE 3
 #define ATOM_MAX_HW_I2C_READ  255

@@ -42,7 +43,10 @@
 	struct drm_device *dev = chan->dev;
 	struct amdgpu_device *adev = drm_to_adev(dev);
 	PROCESS_I2C_CHANNEL_TRANSACTION_PS_ALLOCATION args;
-	int index = GetIndexIntoMasterTable(COMMAND, ProcessI2cChannelTransaction);
+	/* PS4 ATOM uses ReadEDIDFromHWAssistedI2C name (ps4gentoo 1fef36f5).
+	 * In current atombios.h this is a #define alias for ProcessI2cChannelTransaction,
+	 * so functionally equivalent; the rename documents PS4 ATOM table-set choice. */
+	int index = GetIndexIntoMasterTable(COMMAND, ReadEDIDFromHWAssistedI2C);
 	unsigned char *base;
 	u16 out = cpu_to_le16(0);
 	int r = 0;
@@ -162,7 +166,9 @@
 void amdgpu_atombios_i2c_channel_trans(struct amdgpu_device *adev, u8 slave_addr, u8 line_number, u8 offset, u8 data)
 {
 	PROCESS_I2C_CHANNEL_TRANSACTION_PS_ALLOCATION args;
-	int index = GetIndexIntoMasterTable(COMMAND, ProcessI2cChannelTransaction);
+	/* PS4 ATOM uses ReadEDIDFromHWAssistedI2C name (ps4gentoo 1fef36f5);
+	 * macro alias for ProcessI2cChannelTransaction in our atombios.h. */
+	int index = GetIndexIntoMasterTable(COMMAND, ReadEDIDFromHWAssistedI2C);

 	args.ucRegIndex = offset;
 	args.lpI2CDataOut = data;
